   "source": [
    "u6_df = u6.copy()\n",
    "u6_df['YEAR'] = u6_df['DATA'].dt.year\n",
    "u6_df['MONTH'] = u6_df['DATA'].dt.month\n",
    "u6_df['DAY'] = u6_df['DATA'].dt.day"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 68,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "u6_df['DATE_TIME'] = pd.to_datetime({'year':u6_df['YEAR'], 'month':u6_df['MONTH'], 'day':u6_df['DAY'], 'hour':u6_df['ORA']})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 69,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "u6_df = u6_df[['DATE_TIME', 'CONSUMO_KWH_U6']]\n",
    "u6_df.columns = ['ds','y']\n",
    "u6_train = u6_df[u6_df['ds']<'2020-06-01']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 70,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "u6_train=u6_train.set_index('ds').resample('D').sum()\n",
    "u6_train.index = u6_train.index.to_period('D')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "m = Prophet(yearly_seasonality=True, weekly_seasonality=True, daily_seasonality=True)\n",
    "m.add_country_holidays(country_name='IT')\n",
    "m.fit(u6_train)\n",
    "future = m.make_future_dataframe(periods=30, freq='D')\n",
    "forecast = m.predict(future)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

    "prima_parte.reset_index(inplace=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "seconda_parte = forecast.reset_index()[['ds','fbProphet Forecast Upper bound']]\n",
    "seconda_parte['ds'] = seconda_parte['ds'].dt.date\n",
    "seconda_parte = seconda_parte.rename(columns = {'fbProphet Forecast Upper bound' : 'y'})\n",
    "seconda_parte['y'] = round(seconda_parte['y']*24,2)"
   ]
  },
  {

    "terza_parte.reset_index(inplace=True)"
   ]
  },
  {

   "metadata": {},

   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 117,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def mean_absolute_percentage_error(y_true, y_pred): \n",
    "    y_true, y_pred = np.array(y_true), np.array(y_pred)\n",
    "    return np.mean(np.abs((y_true - y_pred) / y_true)) * 100"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 44,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mape = mean_absolute_percentage_error(u1_train['y'], fitted['fbProphet Forecast'])"
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Stima rolling"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 88,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "u1_train = u1_df[u1_df['ds'] < '2020-03-01']\n",
    "u1_test = u1_df[u1_df['ds'] >= '2020-03-01']\n",
    "u1_test = u1_test.set_index('ds').resample(rule='d').sum()\n",
    "u1_train = u1_train.set_index('ds').resample(rule='d').sum()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 90,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "auto=auto_arima(u1_train)\n",
    "param=auto.order"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 104,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "history = [x for x in u1_train['y']]\n",
    "predictions = list()\n",
    "for t in range(len(u1_test)):\n",
    "    model = ARIMA(history, order=param)\n",
    "    model_fit = model.fit()\n",
    "    output = model_fit.forecast()\n",
    "    yhat = output[0]\n",
    "    predictions.append(yhat)\n",
    "    obs = u1_test.iloc[t].y\n",
    "    history.append(obs)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 105,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "u1_test['predictions']=predictions\n",
    "u1_test['predictions']=u1_test['predictions'].astype('float')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 118,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "5.836450329261608"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 118,

     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [

    "mape"

   "source": [
    "final=pd.concat([u1_train,u1_test], axis=0)"
   ]
